
LAB 03 QUESTION:

1.Write a socket program in C to implement the following

Server opens a port, creates the TCP socket, and goes into "wait for connection" state, and actively listens for socket connections.

Client logs into the system by connecting to the server on the appropriate port

Client sends username

Server checks to see if it is a new user or existing user and requests a password

Client sends password

Server either registers a new user or checks to see if the password matches. Server then sends acknowledgement to the client

Note:

Store users and their username and passwords in array or in a file

Multiple clients should be able to register.

2. Create Client -Server implement chat until exit command
Implement Iterative server -client (Chat program)
